                    <m>41_8=4\times 8^1+1\times 8^0=32+1=33</m>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <m>764_8=7\times 8^2+6\times 8^1+4\times 8^0=448+48+4=500</m>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <m>1011_8=1\times 8^3+0\times 8^2+1\times 8^1+1\times 8^0=512+0+8+1=521</m>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <m>25073_8=2\times 8^4+5\times 8^3+0\times 8^2+7\times 8^1+3\times 8^0=8192+2560+0+56+3=10811</m>
                  </li>
                </ol>
              </p>
            </answer>
          </example>
          <example>
            <statement>
              <p>
                Use the technique of the previous example to write the following numbers in expanded form and then express them in base ten.
                <ol>
                  <li>
                    <m>210_3</m>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <m>11001_2</m>
                  </li>
