        <subsection xml:id="ssec-boolean-syntax-python">
          <title>Boolean Syntax in Python</title>
          <p>
            Python allows you to perform logical operations on Boolean variables in the way that you would expect, as you can see in the interactive window below. (The print() statements are needed to convince the underlying interpreter to display output.  In a typical python shell, they are not needed.)
            <sage language="python">
              <input>
                print(True or False)
                print(True and False)
                print(not True)
                print(not False)
                print(1 and 0)
                print(1 or 0)
              </input>
              <output>
                True
                False
                False
                True
                0
                1
              </output>
            </sage>
          </p>
        </subsection>
